{"name": "arnoldas-a-mod1-atsiskaitymas", "metadata": {"name": "arnoldas-a-mod1-atsiskaitymas", "version": "0.1.0", "classifiers": [], "home_page": "https://github.com/Asasai001/arnoldas-a-mod1-atsiskaitymas", "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["selenium", "pandas"], "summary": "A Python project for scraping book info and football results", "upload_time": 1732556064}, "documentation": ["# **arnoldas_a_mod1_atsiskaitymas**\r\n\r\nPackage for scraping book information and football match results from specified websites.\r\n\r\n# **Installation**\r\npip install arnoldas-a-mod1-atsiskaitymas\r\n\r\n# **Usage**\r\nA package is using selenium for web scraping and supports data export in CSV and dictionary formats. **IMPORTANT**. In order to use a package, user needs to install Chrome WebDriver\r\nand Update the path in the football_results.py and book_info.py files from path = 'C:\\\\Tools\\\\chromedriver\\\\chromedriver.exe' to yours\r\n\r\n# **Parameters**\r\nA package can be run from main, user has to determine:\r\n- source = \"book_info\" or \"football_results\"\r\n- timeout = in seconds\r\n- return_format = \"dict\" or \"csv\"\r\n\r\n# **Example**\r\n\r\n```python\r\nfrom arnoldas_a_mod1_atsiskaitymas.crawler import Crawl\r\n\r\ndef main():\r\n    source = \"book_info\"\r\n    timeout = 60\r\n    return_format = \"dict\"\r\n\r\n    results = Crawl(source=source, timeout=timeout, return_format=return_format).web_results()\r\n    if results:\r\n        print(\"Gauti duomenys:\")\r\n        print(results)\r\n\r\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\r\n    main()\r\n"], "modules": [{"name": "tests.test_book_info", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "tests.test_book_info.TestBookInfo", "bases": ["unittest.TestCase"], "methods": [{"name": "tests.test_book_info.TestBookInfo.test_book_info", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "mock_chrome", "type": null, "defaul